            "doi": "10.1093/bioinformatics/btx057",
            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "\u00a9 The Author 2017. Published by Oxford University Press.Motivation: Variant call format (VCF) files document the genetic variation observed after DNA sequencing, alignment and variant calling of a sample cohort. Given the complexity of the VCF format as well as the diverse variant annotations and genotype metadata, there is a need for fast, flexible methods enabling intuitive analysis of the variant data within VCF and BCF files. Results: We introduce cyvcf2, a Python library and software package for fast parsing and querying of VCF and BCF files and illustrate its speed, simplicity and utility.",
